race.comment: ELRONTE (6) led for the judge and gave a kick but was overwhelmed close to home when resuming over this distance at Toowoomba last start. Led all the way to win with ease second-up last prep at Gatton. Sure to take plenty of catching. DARLING TAKE CARE (4) opened this prep with four top-three finishes, all at five furlongs, before a modest effort at the Gold Coast last time. Gets in nicely under today's scale so a return to form will not surprise. The sparingly raced filly CALL TO COURAGE (7) opened her account in a Lismore maiden over 1110m recently. Speedy three-year-old who should enjoy a lovely trail today so another big run seems likely. EXTREME SPIRIT (1) has been freshened up since a moderate effort over 1200m at Ipswich on 26 November. Hasn't won for almost three years but his best figures measure up - one for the exotics. AQUATIER (3) failed first-up at Eagle Farm but can improve back to her pet trip in an easier race.
